The paper deals with a problem in computational geometry, specifically finding the maximum area parallelogram inside a convex polygon. Therefore, cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves proving new structural properties of the maximum area parallelogram, which could fall under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics). The discussion of applications of the result suggests that it could also be relevant to cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) and cs.CC (Computational Complexity).
